<br>
The ability has a 1 second refresh, and a cast time of approximately 4 seconds, so the refresh is for all purposes instant.<br>
<br>
When trained, the ability allows you to make a hotkey.  When clicked, a cast time bar appears and after four seconds your pet poofs ('By your command, master.').  When clicked again, after four seconds your pet returns to life ('I live again...').  The ability does not make a gem or create any tangible representation of the stored pet.<br>
<br>
When you have a stored pet, you may cast another pet.  If you try and restore your original pet while you have a second pet up, you get the &quot;You cannot have more than one pet at a time.&quot; message, but your original pet is not lost, it can still be restored when your second pet dies.<br>
<br>
The stored pet is lost completely on zoning.  Invis does not cause your stored pet to poof.<br>
<br>
You can not store your pet when he has any kind of agro ('Your pet is the focus of something's attention.'), regardless of the amount of hate or distance from hater -- the same rules as Summon Companion.  You can however restore the pet while mobs are hitting you, this could be our escape spell. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=86775"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/deadgnome.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=perilbane>Perilbane</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#333333>(10/26/02 1:20:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm30.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=408.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Suspend Minion I</span><hr size=1> If the pet restores at your side... it could also be a way to make a pet, suspend it, go invis to run to a spot, then restore the pet there.<br>
